That part which until 1894 formed part of the parish of Saddleworth. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

That part within the borough of Mossley, which was added to 
    Lancashire in 1889 and was added to the parish of Mossley in 1894.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Saddleworth in Quickmere 
    Middle Division Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1937 and added to the parish 
    of Saddleworth.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Saddleworth in Upper 
    Mill Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1900 and added to the parish of Saddleworth.
